    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is an exceptional survivor, featuring the original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The apex seals and internal housings show optimal health, with recent compression tests yielding high, consistent pulses across all chambers. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise short-throw five-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring power delivery is both visceral and controlled. Its lightweight chassis retains the original double-wishbone suspension configuration, free of bushing fatigue or geometry deviations. The vacuum-operated sequential boost transition is seamless, a rarity for this platform, indicating a meticulously maintained solenoid rack. Finished in its original pigment with a flawless interior, this FD represents a pinnacle of 50/50 weight distribution and analog feedback, devoid of any aftermarket modifications or structural imperfections.",
